</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhionsligo>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1200<br> <font color=#333333>(11/12/02 4:57:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Slow &gt;&gt; All</span><hr size=1> No one said you had to go to PoP for experience guys.  You want the best experience?  Well there's a price for it.  Get an optimal group.  PoP is tough.  That's all there is to it.<br>
<br>
No we should *never* get any form of slow, not even slow on summoned weapons.  That's absurd.  All of our utility, with the exception of summoned bandages, is either neutral by nature or is geared towards offensive damage.  We are an offensive class.  We get no root, blah blah blah, you've all heard this before.  And therefore we will most certainly not get slow.  Sorry guys, you're playing the wrong pet class.  You want slow, go play a beastlord.<br>
<br>
Enough of this guys.  There are 3 major classes with slow, (3/15 is 1/5 of all the classes).  There are 6 group slots.  You're telling me that the best experience in the game should just be handed to you on a silver platter?  Come on.  It's not too difficult to find a slower as it is.  Guess what, you also need a healer for these groups.  Should we heal people too?  By your logic that we need a slower, and therefore mages should be able to slow....well, we should be able to heal too. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
