</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chakkolio>Chakkolio</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#333333>(11/12/02 5:02:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=26>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Slow &gt;&gt; All</span><hr size=1> they've already begun the only change they'll make to really have an effect on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>slow</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, even if it doesnt work correctly at this time.<br>
<br>
Ideally (read: when it works) some mobs will mitigate slow to varying degrees, most likely based on mob level and difficulty.  Granted that at this time slow is screwed on some mobs, if/when they get it to work, slow will still be helpful but wont be the godly skill/spell it is now.<br>
<br>
I do understand however thats it unlikely normal exp mobs will mitigate slow so much as raid type minibosses and gods.  And undoubtedly, some will moan and complain that its still unbalanced in the exp game -- so what?  You want to slow?  Enc/Shm/Bst ... have fun PL to 60 and then pull out ur slow spells and have a blast.  Mages arent meant to slow, mages arent going to get pets that effectively replace lvl 65 player classes (i.e. warriors) and pets arent going to get a CH spell for their summons.<br>
<br>
(52) Transon's E Infusion - 580hp healed for 275mana<br>
(60) Transon's E Renewal - 900hp healed for 400mana<br>
(64) Planar Renewal - 1200hp healed for 300mana<br>
<br>
Planar renewal is already a great heal spell, and much better (and far easier to obtain) than the lvl 60 heal spell that every magician under the sun moans about not getting.  While spectral parchments dont grow on trees or rain down from the sky, they're far more common than a possible drop off Grieg, a boss rarely killed nowadays.  So put in your time, wish for a bit of luck, and you'll get Planar Renewal.  I got it the first time i handed in a Spectral Parchment.  Its a great spell, and along with the new pets that regen for 3-5% / tic, there is no need for a pet CH*<br>
<br>
If you find yourself in the situation where ur pet needs CH'ing regularly, then you're either hunting mobs you shouldnt be hunting, or doing something else wrong.  The pet serves as a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">diversion</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> while we 'drop bombs' on the mobs.  The pet shouldnt be made to sit their and deal the damage while we toss in 1 nuke and rake in the exp.  Note i said <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>shouldnt</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> because I know this is what pets have become over time.  I know pets are our only true defense, I know, but I dont think most magicians see what their pet truly is, only what they wish their pet to be.<br>
<br>
For those rare situations where you find that you really could use a CH spell for your pet, spend 5 AA points and buy Mend Companion.  I know it has a re-use time (recently lowered) but it can further be lowered by buying Hastened Mend PoP AA skill.  So Mend + pet heals + pet regen should be good enough, as the magician in question should kill the mob before the pet needs a CH.  Does this always happen?  Of course not that would be too easy, not exciting at all.  But if we're all about DPS, then we shouldnt need CHs for our pseudo-tanks.<br>
<br>
*how rare do you think a pet CH would be if they implemented it.  It certainly wouldnt be vendor sold, and with all the complaints I see daily about parchment drops, I can only imagine how more upset players would be if there was a spell out there but they couldnt get it, as opposed to being no spell at all and just wishing for it. <p><p align="center"><font face="Tahoma"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7621>Chakkolio<a/><BR>Arch Convoker<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chakkolio>Chakkolio</A> at: 11/12/02 5:19:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#333333>(11/12/02 5:23:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Slow &gt;&gt; All</span><hr size=1> I don't want slow either.<br>
